Share the Spirit of DIWALI Vizag Needs YOUSS Rajamouli's short film for Cyclone Hudhud victimsDirector S.S. Rajamouli, who is busy with his film Baahubali, has made time to come up with a short film for Hudhud victims. The two-minute short film titled Share the Spirit of Diwali — Vizag Needs You, features character artiste Prithvi and other new faces.The film, which is doing the rounds on social media, urges people to donate to the CM’s Relief Fund. The director says, “A small gesture can go a long way in reducing someone’s pain.Can we do something to lessen the pain of our brothers in Vizag? TOLLYWOOD : FLASH NEWSFire Accident At Baahubali Sets, 4 InjuredBaahubali's shooting hit by fire mishapDirector Rajamouli's magnum opus Baahubali's shooting is progressing at brisk pace in Ramoji Film City, Hyderabad. The film's shooting was hit by a mishap on Saturday evening. While the filmmakers were shooting war scenes on the crew in RFC, fire accident occurred and four fighters suffered minor burns.This resulted in fire. Four fighters who were waiting for their chance to participate in fire scenes were standing next to the equipment and caught fire. Fighters Santosh, Paandu, Ganesh and Santosh suffered minor injuries and received first aid in a private hospital in Hayath Nagar.Film stars Prabhas, Rana, Anushka and Tamannaah in lead roles. M.M.Keeravani is the music director for the film produced by Arka Media Works banner.
